sql:
SELECT classification_label
FROM image_classifications
WHERE classification_id = 1;

SELECT classification_label, confidence_level
FROM image_classifications
WHERE classification_status = 'confirmed';

SELECT AVG(confidence_level) AS average_confidence_level
FROM image_classifications
WHERE classification_status = 'confirmed';

SELECT image_id, count1
FROM cct_xc_class_000_counts
WHERE count_unit = 'regions';

SELECT image_id, SUM(count1) AS total_count1
FROM cct_xc_class_000_counts
GROUP BY image_id;

SELECT patient_name 
FROM patients 
WHERE patient_id = (SELECT patient_id FROM images WHERE image_id = 0);

external_knowledge:
- 'Image details' refers to the unique identifier, patient ID, and type of medical image (e.g., X-ray, MRI, CT scan); 
- 'Reviewed annotations' refer to the text of annotations that have been reviewed by researchers; 
- 'Confirmed classifications' refer to the labels assigned to the images by an AI model and confirmed by researchers; 
- 'Collaboration counts' refer to the number of collaborations between researcher 1 and researcher 2 for each image; 
- 'Reviewed annotations count' and 'confirmed classifications count' refer to the number of reviewed annotations and confirmed classifications per image.

